Former Surgeon-General, Vejay Ramlakan, is being remembered as a brave and remarkable warrior. Courtesy of #DStv403 DURBAN - Nelson Mandela's long-time doctor, Lieutenant-General Vejaynand Ramlakan, was laid to rest in Durban on Saturday. READ: Former SANDF Surgeon General Vejay Ramlakan dies The former Surgeon General of the South African National Defence Force and former MK soldier was given a funeral with full military honours. Health Minister, Zweli Mkhize paid tribute to Nelson Mandela's long-time doctor, at his funeral. Ramlakan died on Thursday last week after a suspected heart attack.